---
import { problemStats } from '../data/research';
import Cite from './Cite.astro';
---

<section id="problem">
  <h2 class="section-title">🔥 SHOCKING FACTS!!! 🔥</h2>
  <p class="center comic">
    How much of your one wild and precious life is going to the little glowing
    rectangle?
  </p>

  {
    problemStats.map((s) => (
      <div class="stat">
        <span class="stat__value">{s.value}</span>
        <span class="stat__label">
          {s.label}
          <Cite source={s.source} />
        </span>
      </div>
    ))
  }

  <div class="inset">
    <p style="margin:0" class="small">
      That's not a moral failing — those apps are engineered by teams of very
      smart people to be exactly this hard to put down. Which is also why
      <b>willpower alone tends to lose</b>. Keep reading. 👇
    </p>
  </div>

  <hr class="rainbow-hr" />
</section>
